// =============================================================================
// Samavāya BI — Query Service
// =============================================================================
// The query service executes queries against datasets (defined in
// core/bi/dataset). It exposes three entry points:
//
//   1. Visual query  — a structured description of fields/filters/groupings
//                      produced by a UI query builder. The canonical input.
//   2. NL query      — natural-language text routed through a pluggable NLProvider
//                      that translates it to a VisualQuery. The NL provider
//                      is out of scope for this service; only the interface lives here.
//   3. Raw expression — a single formula to evaluate, used by calculated-field
//                      previews and ad-hoc "what-if" widgets.
//
// This service is the only place that knows how to produce SQL from a
// VisualQuery. Dataset definitions + relationships + permissions are
// fetched from the dataset service at execute time; row-level security
// is applied as implicit WHERE predicates.
//
// Related docs
// ------------
//   * docs/BI_CONSOLIDATION_ROADMAP.md — Sprint 4 is the implementation
//   * docs/adr/0001-bi-platform-consolidation.md
//   * docs/adr/0003-formula-parser-grammar.md (pending, Sprint 4)
// =============================================================================

